## SF5-103 — Canvas Interaction UX ✅

### What was built

**`Canvas.tsx` (modified)**
- Imports `useViewportStore` for zoom/pan state
- **Wheel zoom**: `onWheel` on the canvas area calls `zoomIn()`/`zoomOut()` based on `deltaY`
- **Pan drag**: Middle-click or Alt+left-click starts a pan drag that calls `viewportStore.panBy()` with per-frame mouse deltas
- **Viewport transform**: A new `.canvas-transform` wrapper div applies `translate(${panX}px, ${panY}px) scale(${zoom})` with `transform-origin: 0 0`
- **Marquee selection**: Left-click drag on empty canvas draws a `.canvas-marquee` overlay rectangle; on mouseup converts screen-space coords to content-space (dividing by zoom, subtracting pan) and calls `selectionStore.selectByRect()`
- **Selected items**: Existing `canvas-item--selected` (2px cyan border) verified working with multi-select
- **Header controls**: Zoom level badge (`100%`), Fit, Reset, +, − buttons
- **Item drag fix**: Mouse deltas now divided by `zoom` so items track pointer correctly at non-1× zoom

**`workspace.css` (modified)**
- `.canvas-transform` — absolute transform container with `transform-origin: 0 0`
- `.canvas-marquee` — dashed cyan border, semi-transparent fill, `pointer-events: none`
- `.canvas-zoom-level` — tabular-nums zoom badge
- `.canvas-ctrl-btn` — viewport control button style
- `.canvas-panel__controls` — flex row for controls in header

**`Canvas.test.tsx` (new)** — 18 tests passing:
- Render / aria-label / transform container presence
- Zoom in/out/reset buttons update store state
- Zoom level display updates reactively
- Fit to canvas button exists
- Items render from visible layers, selected items get `--selected` class
- Marquee overlay appears on drag and disappears on mouseup
- Empty state shows/hides correctly